# FOSS & Privacy Compliance

## License

- Pure FOSS under MIT license
- No proprietary closed-source SDKs in production path

## Distribution

- GitHub Releases as primary channel (portable EXE + WiX MSI)

## Privacy & Telemetry

- Opt-in only telemetry — never enabled by default
- No PII in logs without explicit user consent
- Update checks contact GitHub Releases API only when user initiates

## Security

- Secrets never committed (Gitleaks pre-commit enforced)
- Dependency scanning via CodeQL and Trivy
- FTP credentials stored in Windows Credential Manager, not plain text
- Input validation at all file path and FTP boundaries
